column9:
Honestly, I don't understand why everyone criticized this game... I really liked it. Yes, this part of C&C is completely different from the previous games. Yes, the developers completely abandoned the usual resource gathering and base building. But this didn't detract from the quality of the game one bit.

[list]
[*] As always, excellent cinematic cutscenes between missions;
[*] New, interesting gameplay built around different types of crawlers;
[*] Very beautiful graphics;
[*] And many other advantages.
[/list]

In conclusion: I recommend it to anyone ready to abandon the familiar base-building style of the previous games.

